<h1 class="uk-h2 uk-heading-divider uk-margin">
    
        
                    Property Ownership Tax (ENFIA) in Greece        
        
    
</h1><div class="uk-panel uk-text-lead uk-margin">Athanasios Rozou</div>
                
            
        
        </div>    
</div>
    
</div>
<div class="uk-grid-margin uk-container uk-container-xsmall">
        <div class="uk-grid tm-grid-expand uk-child-width-1-1">    
        
<div class="uk-width-1-1">
    
        
            
            
            
                
                    <div class="uk-panel uk-margin" id="template-bK9ZyCAt#0"><h2 style="text-align: justify;">The Unified Property Ownership Tax (ENFIA) is a mandatory property tax in Greece established in 2014.</h2>
<p style="text-align: justify;">This tax applies to all property types throughout the country, including buildings, residential lots, and agricultural land. The amount due is calculated based on each property's size, location, and specific characteristics. ENFIA is assessed annually on all properties owned as of January 1st. The tax calculation uses the information recorded in your Property Data Declaration (E9 form), which must be accurately filed with the Greek tax authorities.</p>
 
<h3 style="text-align: justify;">myAADEapp: Mobile Tax Management for Property Owners in Greece</h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The «myAADEapp» is the official mobile application of the Independent Authority for Public Revenue (AADE) in Greece, specifically designed to enhance tax management convenience for foreign property owners. This authorized digital platform enables non-resident property investors to monitor their tax account status and execute payments through credit card transactions or the IRIS payment system, with immediate crediting of outstanding obligations.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The application provides foreign property owners with the capability to update their banking information by modifying the IBAN associated with their account, ensuring efficient processing of any tax refunds. Users maintain comprehensive access to their appointment schedules, review the status of previously submitted inquiries to AADE, and receive all official communications directly through the platform.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">A particularly valuable feature for international property owners is the myWallet section, where essential documentation including tax certificates and clearance statements can be downloaded and securely stored for future reference. The application delivers personalized, timely notifications regarding relevant tax matters affecting foreign-owned properties in Greece, ensuring compliance with local regulations regardless of the owner's geographic location.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">This mobile solution serves as a complementary tool to the main myAADE portal, offering streamlined property tax management functionality optimized for smartphones and tablets, catering to the mobile needs of the international property investment community in Greece.</p>
<h3 style="text-align: justify;">ENFIA Payment Procedure</h3>
<h4 style="text-align: justify;">Application Installation</h4>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Begin by downloading the official "myAADEapp" application from the App Store or Google Play Store. This application serves as the authorized mobile platform of the Greek Independent Authority for Public Revenue (Ανεξάρτητη Αρχή Δημοσίων Εσόδων or ΑΑΔΕ).</p>
<h4 style="text-align: justify;">Authentication Process</h4>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Upon installation, proceed to authenticate using your designated username and password credentials. For clients who have acquired property through our services, we have previously communicated these authentication details to facilitate your access to the platform.</p>
<h4 style="text-align: justify;">Payment Navigation</h4>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Access your tax obligations by navigating through the following pathway: My Account &gt; Debts and Payments &gt; Payment of Non-Settled Debts. The financial amount displayed in this section represents your annual property tax assessment (ENFIA). Continue the payment process by selecting "Next" and following the guided instructions to complete your transaction using a debit card.</p>
<h4 style="text-align: justify;">Important Timeline Considerations</h4>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The Greek tax authorities typically issue the Annual Property Tax assessment between February and March each year. We strongly recommend recording this financial obligation in your calendar system to ensure timely compliance with Greek property tax regulations.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Your prompt attention to this annual requirement will maintain your property's good standing with Greek tax authorities and prevent any potential penalties associated with delayed payments.</p></div>
